cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.AR

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper discusses the deployment of computations to serverless backends in the cloud, which involves distributed computing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a practical resource management policy for serverless computing, which is related to software engineering practices. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the resource allocation and provisioning in serverless computing, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the characteristics of the FaaS workload and proposes a resource management policy, which are related to programming language design and implementation. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): Although not the main focus of the paper, the resource allocation and provisioning in serverless computing can also be related to hardware architecture design.
